            <title>[CASSANDRA-16898] The clustering order logic in Materialized view creation changed in 4.0</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-16898</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Before 4.0, when a Materialized view was created with no &lt;tt&gt;CLUSTERING ORDER&lt;/tt&gt; specified the clustering order was based on the base table clustering order (see &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/blob/cassandra-3.11/src/java/org/apache/cassandra/cql3/statements/CreateViewStatement.java#L108&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;3.11 code&lt;/a&gt;). In 4.0 this behaviour changed and the clustering order was defaulted to ASC for all columns. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
